      The top 3 highest and lowest points indicated are based only on feedback from others - they do not take into account your self-evaluation).
      <br> The top 3 items are those items with the highest scores – regarding these, evaluators don’t believe any change is needed (i.e., you do not need to do anymore or less)
      <br> The top 3 development points are the 3 items with a low score – here, evaluators see the biggest need for change.
      <br>To make sure that these items represent you top 3 strenghts and development points you have to look for them in the “dive in deep” section at the end of this report. Here you can see if your raters indicate if these behaviors are at the right level, if you need to show them more or less. This will define if they are strengths or development points
    </p>
